To maintain this code properly, the following three repositories have to be
tracked for changes (maintenance details below):

- https://github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3
- https://github.com/sqlcipher/sqlcipher
- https://github.com/libtom/libtomcrypt


Update code from https://github.com/mattn/go-sqlite3
----------------------------------------------------

Current release: v1.14.34

1. git clone mattn/go-sqlite3 new version to temp dir
2. Use ./track_go-sqlite3.sh <mattn/go-sqlite3 dir>
3. find & sed mattn/go-sqlite3 to AnoRebel/go-sqlcipher
4. rewrite pragma args golang code to sqlite3.go
   - _pragma_key (MUST execute before all other PRAGMAs)
   - _pragma_cipher_page_size
   - _pragma_cipher_compatibility
5. Add #include <stdint.h> to the C includes in sqlite3.go


Update code from https://github.com/sqlcipher/sqlcipher
-------------------------------------------------------

Current release: v4.14.0

Note:
v4.14.0 restored LibTomCrypt support (it was removed in v4.12.0).
If a future version removes it again, revert the corresponding commit
(see https://github.com/sqlcipher/sqlcipher/issues/564).

Execute:
1. git clone sqlcipher to temp dir
2. git checkout v4.14.0
3. ./configure --with-tempstore=yes \
     CFLAGS="-DSQLITE_HAS_CODEC \
             -DSQLITE_EXTRA_INIT=sqlcipher_extra_init \
             -DSQLITE_EXTRA_SHUTDOWN=sqlcipher_extra_shutdown \
             -DSQLCIPHER_CRYPTO_LIBTOMCRYPT"
4. make sqlite3.c
5. Copy sqlite3.c and sqlite3.h
6. Fix const qualifier warnings in sqlite3.c:
   - strrchr() and strchr() return const char* when given const char*,
     add explicit (char*) cast where assigned to non-const


